				<h2 class="article-title">Coursework</h2>
				<p>A coursework pertains to the work perform by students at middle/high school or university, which contributes to their overall grade. (Source: Urban Dictionary)</p>
				<p>However, coursework is graded separately from the final exams. It commonly involves research or experimental work. Coursework can comprise of book reports, essays, or dissertations. Unlike exams, students have several days or weeks to accomplish their assignments. They are also allowed to use notes, Internet, and textbooks for research. Coursework is considered as one of the numerous modes of assessment.</p>
				
