		<p class="main-article">Professors ask students to produce a coursework to broaden their knowledge and enhance their research skill. In addition, coursework offers students an avenue to apply the theoretical knowledge that they learned from school. There are instances when coursework is performed by groups to teach students to interact and coordinate with each other. However, most students are confronted with the issues of plagiarism. A coursework undertaken by a group of professionals who work in a writing company is guaranteed to be free from plagiarism.</p>
		<h4 class="process-title blue">What are possible coursework problems?</h4>
		<p class="main-article">Students may fail to accomplish their coursework due to some problems. The common problems confronting most students are the following:</p>
		<h4 class="process-title blue">Plagiarism</h4>
		<p class="main-article">Plagiarism pertains to the failure of students to properly cite another author’s ideas, thoughts, expressions, and language in an original work. There is a tendency for students to present these ideas, thoughts, expressions, and language as their own. Some students thought that taking someone’s work and modifying it a bit makes it an original work. There is a probability of copying significant portions of a single source without any attempt for minimal alterations. There are students who utilized various sources without paraphrasing and citing these sources. There are also instances when the student utilized his/her previous work.</p>
		<p class="main-article">Issues of plagiarism also arise when students fail to include the location of the referenced material. It is still considered as plagiarism even if he/she mentioned the name of the author as a source. There are instances when students fail to provide accurate information about the source. Thus, there is a tendency for students to unknowingly commit plagiarism. Several students are not familiar with the bounds of what can be considered as plagiarism or not. Thus, it becomes beneficial to seek the aid of a writing company with professional staff members who possess the necessary experience and skill to produce high quality papers.</p>
		<h4 class="process-title blue">Lack of Time </h4>
		<p class="main-article">Coursework usually needs to be submitted on a given time frame. Some students fail to submit their assignments on the specified deadline due to certain problems, time constraints, and important obligations. Students can submit their paper on the specified deadline when they organize their workload or plan ahead.</p>
		<h4 class="process-title blue">Difficulty in Expressing Ideas through Written Words</h4>
		<p class="main-article">Some students have difficulty in expressing ideas through written words. It takes experience and skill to cohesively organize words and sentences in an essay.</p>
		<h4 class="process-title blue">Committing Technical Errors </h4>
		<p class="main-article">Students may not be fully familiar with the subject-verb agreement, which increases the probability of committing grammatical errors. They may also incorrectly cite and reference the sources. Committing these errors often cause lower grades. </p>
